  "linkedinUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/activity-7449610541993578497-9ZJH",
  "content": "Space doesn’t forgive hardware failures. AMD is building silicon that survives.\n\nRadiation-tolerant Versal adaptive SoCs powering Blue Origin’s lunar lander, NASA’s Perseverance rover, OSIRIS-REx, and Japan’s first optical satellite constellation — all validated for the harshest environment known to electronics.\nWhat that actually means in practice:\n• Proton, heavy ion, and gamma radiation testing \n• MIL-PRF-38535 qualified \n• Fault-tolerant system design support\n• Long-term lifecycle support aligned with multi-decade missions\n\nAnd unlike traditional space ASICs, these are reconfigurable — update algorithms post-launch, deploy new AI models mid-mission, adapt to changing requirements without new hardware.\n\nRad-hard + adaptive SoC is a powerful combination when your hardware is 384,000 km away.\n\n\\@AMD #AMD #FPGA #SpaceFrontier #RadiationHard #togetherweadvance_space exploration #AMDBrandAmbassador",
