{
  "type": "post",
  "id": "7445937901969776640",
  "linkedinUrl": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/brendawilsondwt_amd-greatopportunity-togetherweadvance-activity-7445937901969776640-PZOD",
  "content": "🚀 Join AMD – Product Manager, Semi-Custom Business Unit 🚀 \n\nAre you ready to be at the center of innovation in high-performance computing and custom silicon solutions? AMD is looking for a dynamic Product Manager to join our Semi-Custom Business Unit, where you’ll play a pivotal role in shaping cutting-edge products for global customers.\nIn this role, you’ll serve as the key bridge between our customers and internal engineering, business, and operations teams—owning and driving the success of complex, high-impact programs from concept to delivery.\n\n🌟 What You’ll Do\nLead end-to-end semi-custom business programs, from strategy through execution\nDrive customer engagement, contract negotiations, and supplier strategies\nBuild and manage business forecasts, P&L, and product roadmaps\nPartner with engineering to deliver next-gen silicon solutions (CPU/GPU, SoCs)\nEnsure operational excellence and continuous supply across global teams\n\n🧠 What You Bring\nExperience in product management, program management, or product marketing within semiconductors, HPC, or graphics\nStrong ability to define MRDs/PRDs, business cases, and product roadmaps\nKnowledge of computer systems, CPU/GPU architectures, or silicon technologies\nProven success managing large, complex customer programs\nExceptional communication, analytical, and problem-solving skills\nAbility to thrive in a fast-paced, cross-functional, matrixed environment\n\nBonus Points:\n ✔️ Experience with procurement/supply chain\n ✔️ Strong negotiation background\n ✔️ Experience managing a P&L\n🌍 Travel: Up to 20% international\n\nAt AMD, you’ll work at the forefront of innovation, helping deliver custom silicon solutions that power the world’s most advanced technologies.\n\n🔗 Ready to make an impact? Apply now and help define the future of computing.\n\nCasey Brewer (Dalman)\n\n#AMD #greatopportunity #togetherweadvance #productmanager #cuttingedgetechnooloty",
